      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "Outgoing longwave radiation during the night will be severely restricted. The surface of the snowpack will cool hardly at all during the overcast night and will soften quickly. This applies on very steep sunny slopes in particular below approximately 2800 m, as well as in all aspects below approximately 2500 m. <br/> <br/> Some rain will fall. These weather conditions will give rise to increasing and thorough wetting of the snowpack. <br/> <br/> Isolated avalanche prone weak layers exist in the top section of the old snowpack. Towards its base, the snowpack consists of faceted crystals. This applies in particular on west, north and east facing slopes at high altitudes and in high Alpine regions."
      },
      "source": {
        "provider": {
          "name": "LWD K\u00e4rnten",
          "website": "https://lawinenwarndienst.ktn.gv.at/?lang=en"
        }
